This article is a transcript of a press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney. He starts by highlighting a bill that House Republicans are trying to pass that would weaken the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB). He explains the importance of the CFPB in protecting consumers from financial abuses. Carney then addresses questions about the President's involvement in drone strikes on American citizens, the President's response to Michael Sam's announcement, the debt ceiling, immigration reform, and other topics. Carney also mentions that the President is excited about the Olympics and that the administration is closely monitoring the situation in Syria.